DefaultDialogue: Be careful when traveling outside the city. An invasionary force gathers out there!
New Corsica is in desperate need of able-bodied heroes. \n\nThe Corrupted Legion will overrun this city unless we can find a way to stop them.
Your courage has given New Corsica a chance to resist Crassus. The people thank you!
They said this was a land of miracles. I had begun to believe it was simply a land of nightmares. \n\nI am glad to see that I was wrong.
You are not familiar to me. And I do not know a Tribune Kraus. \n\nWhere is everyone? What happened to the fort?
You are not familiar to me. And I do not know a Tribune Kraus. \n\nWhere is everyone? What happened to the fort?
So much has changed. How could I have been dreaming for so long? \n\nI must gather my wits about me…

Prefect Drusilla commands these soldiers. She’s a bloodthirsty warmonger who serves only her own ambition. \n\nI always considered her a disgrace to the Legion. The Corruption must have found its way into the 19th through her.
Drusilla has a bodyguard named Magnus. He’s a giant of a Gaul who could kill most men with his bare hands. \n\nThe other centurions greatly fear and respect him. He is a symbol of Drusilla’s power.
The success of your raids has left the camp in disarray! Drusilla will seek to close ranks with her tribunes. \n\nShe’s always so predictable.
Drusilla must feel as if she’s stalked by Nemesis herself. \n\nI wouldn’t be surprised if the invasion of New Corsica was entirely her design.
I humbly beg your pardon. \n\nThis letter… comes as a terrible shock…
The defense of New Corsica continues. Steel yourself for the coming conflict.
There you are, friend! I’ve spoken to Prefect Severan. He’s recalling the remaining Praetorians and securing the city. \n\nDid you speak to Charmion?
There are many evils that plague this land. Soon there will have to be a reckoning.

I wanted to believe that the noble man who sacrificed so much, the loyal soul who loved friends and family, the champion who diligently protected the people of New Corsica, still existed. \n\nBut I must face the truth.
Hail, hero of New Corsica! Your deeds shall endure as long as the stars!
Hail, Hero of New Corsica! Always good to see you. \n\nForgive me if I seem preoccupied. I am finding the business of running a city a bit overwhelming.
I still can’t believe Queen Cleopatra’s alive. The city rejoices at her return! \n\nI wish my father could've been here to witness this moment.
There is no doubt in my mind, you were sent by the gods. You are a hero out of myth. \n\nYou will forever have an ally and friend in me.
Welcome to New Corsica, stranger. \n\nI apologize for the state of our city but we live in troubled times.
Welcome to New Corsica, stranger. \n\nI apologize for the state of our city but we live in troubled times.
Word of your remarkable deeds is spreading, noble warrior. \n\nNew Corsica salutes you!
This is the dawning of a new day for our city and our people. \n\nThere will be great work ahead of us, but we are up to the challenge.
The gods prepare to return, stranger! They judge our every deed, word, and thought! \n\nDo not anger them, lest you suffer their divine wrath!
New Corsica has lost its way! We have displeased the gods and now evil sweeps over these lands led by a terrible demon!
If we do not prove ourselves worthy, the gods will never return! We must prepare the way! \n\nAn age of enlightenment awaits us!
What will become of us? Repent before it is too late! I pray the gods have mercy upon us all!
Be warned, New Corsica! The tyrant’s son has returned! \n\nWe must be vigilant! There is a venomous serpent in our midst!
I must prepare the way… I do this for you, my beloved… enlightenment will come to the people…
Greetings, pilgrim. The gods once inhabited this holy site. Tread with reverence for they are watching.
The idols here were once vessels for the gods. The Pontifex believes that with the proper holy relic, we may call upon their power to aid us in our time of need.

The relic’s dimensions must be precise. 

A hand in length, a palm in breadth, two digits in height… 

Yes, that’s correct!
There! The holy relic is done. It’s far more beautiful than I imagined. \n\nI put the hope of New Corsica in your hands, noble hero.
I have failed the people of New Corsica and exposed you to terrible danger. \n\nPlease forgive my unworthiness.
Please allow me time for quiet reflection. \n\nI must pray for forgiveness and seek to atone for my failure.
One thing has become clear to me: The Pontifex has lost her reason. The long centuries have proven too much for her mind. \n\nFor her, immortality proved to be a curse.
Oh goodness, it seems the Pontifex once loved Crassus. She calls him by his first name, Lucius. \n\nShe’s even written romantic poetry about him…
According to the Codex, the Prime Key can be reassembled in something called the Forge of Ptah. \n\nIt requires a special code to ignite it but I believe that code can be found near the forge itself.
With the Prime Key, I believe we now have hope of stopping Crassus and preventing another curse from being unleashed upon the land.
There you are! I’ve finished translating the glyphs in the Forge of Ptah. \n\nI know the purpose of the Prime Key.
The gods of this land bless you, noble hero. You are truly their chosen champion.
I am filled with joy! I never thought I’d live to see such a wondrous event. \n\nAnd it’s all thanks to you, my non-believer.
How is an honest, hardworking merchant to make a living under these wretched conditions? \n\nIt’s a disgrace to New Corsica and to our patrons.
Look at this wreckage! It’s a disgrace! Where are the blasted Praetorians? \n\nNew Corsica’s already battered reputation may not survive this latest calamity!
Well, I still insist that monster was a manticore! And you singlehandedly destroyed it! \n\nWhy, your legend will outshine even that of noble Evandrus!
I am here on official Marauder business. I have no time to trifle with you. \n\nWhy don't you come back when you've got some guts!
Well met, fellow Marauder! \n\nWhat trophies have you taken lately?
Pah, you're in the wrong place. \n\nGo beg the gods for help, or whatever it is you do.
Walk back the way you came. \n\nUnless you're looking for a good fight…
Ah, the sight of you warms this old warrior's heart. \n\nKeep winning glory, for mighty Mars and the Marauders!
Begone! I have time only for those who crave knowledge. \n\nThe Syndicate keeps to our own.
Ah, excuse me, I was lost in thought. \n\nHow might the Syndicate serve you?
Spare me your misguided idealism. \n\nMy time is too valuable to waste with you.
You're looking for Commander Maximo, Marauder. \n\nMy words would be meaningless to you.
Ah, excuse me, I was lost in thought. \n\nHow might the Syndicate serve you?
Those who are truly blind cannot see even in the light. \n\nOnce you have taken the scales from your eyes and sided with the Covenant, then we may do business.
If you always give, you will always have. \n\nWhat may I give you, devotee?
Those who live by the sword will perish by it. \n\nBe on your way, Marauder.
Are you here to make amends for your hubris? \n\nLet me know if you change your mind.
You are a beacon of hope and life in these trying times. \n\nEvery deed, from the humble to the great, kindles the light in all of us.
The Legion's at our door, and the Ancients are rampaging across the sands. \n\nLet us drink and laugh while we can!
PLACEHOLDER
Hearken to me, traveler! \n\nThese roads are dangerous. Be on your guard!
Praise the gods! \n\nI’ve been desperate to send word to New Corsica. The Praetorians assigned to this camp are missing, and I couldn't abandon this post.
Malatesta joined the Praetorians a few years ago. There were some problems at first and he almost mustered out. \n\nEventually, he overcame his personal demons and rose quickly through the ranks.
Prefect Severan must be informed of the situation here. \n\nThe roads are more perilous than ever. I wish I had better news.
The defense of our roads will continue. \n\nOh, should you encounter any Corrupted or Lost on the roads, I’d appreciate you eliminating the threat.
You have entered a desperate battlefield, stranger! \n\nBe ready to defend yourself against the Corrupted!
Crassus has split his legion. He has taken the First Cohort to assault Akhet. \n\nI believe he intends to invade the sacred temple as he did centuries ago.
Your courage and skill are inspiring, but the sight of those siege engines darkens my hopes. \n\nThe 19th Legion is a formidable enough enemy without them.
Well done, noble hero! \n\nThis Hydra’s Breath will burn those blasted siege weapons to the ground!
You must find the noble Evandrus Crassus! He may prove a great ally to our cause!
Your deeds will never be forgotten! \n\nNew Corsica would be fortunate to have you as a citizen!
This place holds many dangers for the unwary. \n\nMake sure your weapon is at the ready, and keep your wits about you.
There is never enough wine around when you need it. \n\nI am simply parched and could do with a cold drink.
Greetings, Seeker. I'm tracking the movements of the 19th Legion. \n\nMy task, I fear, will never be finished.
My farm was all but destroyed the last time I needed to travel to New Corsica. \n\nI swear, I never know what will happen next when I am away. But I must visit the city for supplies.
I hope you have paid your taxes recently! \n\nIf you have, you needn't worry about a visit from me, Caeso, Frumen of New Corsica!
Welcome to the Thermae, my friend - the finest place to rest in all of Brimstone Sands!
Thank you for the delivery… and your discretion. \n\nFor you, the baths are complimentary!
PLACEHOLDER
Well, you certainly seem to have stirred up this hornet’s nest, youngster! \n\nSadly, I find myself a prisoner of these elemental beings or else I’d offer my assistance.
Well, you certainly seem to have stirred up this hornet’s nest, youngster! \n\nSadly, I find myself a prisoner of these elemental beings or else I’d offer my assistance.
Brilliantly done, youngster! I could tell by your show of martial prowess that you are highly trained. \n\nNow, let me guess – Ghazi sent you. Am I right?
Brilliantly done, youngster! I could tell by your show of martial prowess that you are highly trained. \n\nNow, let me guess – Ghazi sent you. Am I right?
As Ghazi noted, the Angry Earth has not been a significant force here for hundreds of years. \n\nTheir fearsome presence has multiplied by a significant factor recently. That never happens by chance.
As Ghazi noted, the Angry Earth has not been a significant force here for hundreds of years. \n\nTheir fearsome presence has multiplied by a significant factor recently. That never happens by chance.
This device is of Ancient make. I recognize the distinctive markings and construction. It’s a focus for some kind of power. \n\nBut I’ve never seen one exactly like this before.
This device is of Ancient make. I recognize the distinctive markings and construction. It’s a focus for some kind of power. \n\nBut I’ve never seen one exactly like this before.

These items are fine specimens. You have an eye for this sort of work, youngster. \n\nPlace the items in the conjuring circle in the areas I’ve marked. Then for your safety, step away. I shall begin the incantation.
Apophis is a Primordial, one of the powerful elders of the Angry Earth. I had believed him banished long ago. \n\nHis return can only mean destruction. Possibly even another Great Purge.
Apophis is a Primordial, one of the powerful elders of the Angry Earth. I had believed him banished long ago. \n\nHis return can only mean destruction. Possibly even another Great Purge.
The scrolls speak of a process that combines the bodies and souls of different creatures together into a chimera. \n\nThis is the blasphemous power that the Ancients used to create the Primordials.
The scrolls speak of a process that combines the bodies and souls of different creatures together into a chimera. \n\nThis is the blasphemous power that the Ancients used to create the Primordials.
The Disks of Atum were used to focus the quintessence harnessed by the Ennead, a vast power source housed within the Great Pyramid of Akhet. \n\nA structure I built for the Ancients long ago.
I must find the Eye of Horus… yes, the Eye is the key… yes, that is the only way…
When he returns, we will suffer his wrath! He will punish us! \n\nI must intercede! I must save the people!
When he returns, we will suffer his wrath! He will punish us! \n\nI must intercede! I must save the people!
I am lost in darkness... \n\nThe abyss swallows me…
I am lost in darkness... \n\nThe abyss swallows me…
You must stop Apophis from awakening Sutekh! \n\nAn Ancient of his power would wreak havoc on this land!
Now that you have the code and the Eye, here is the location of Sutekh’s Necropolis. \n\nIt was hidden long ago to ensure the slumbering Ancient would not be disturbed.
Now that you have the code and the Eye, here is the location of Sutekh’s Necropolis. \n\nIt was hidden long ago to ensure the slumbering Ancient would not be disturbed.
Yes! Blessed be the Light of Ra! I sensed the foul presence of Apophis banished to the sands! \n\nI was hoping I would not have to confront the demon myself.
I’m afraid I must ask you for one final boon. Given what you’ve done, I feel almost selfish making this request. \n\nBut I would trust only you to undertake this most important task.

It is good to see hope restored to these sands, but I must confess that I am troubled by the reactivation of the Ennead.\n\nKnowing that Artemis is involved and that she sought to raise Sutekh… it does not bode well.
Keep your senses honed, my friend. \n\nI may need to travel to other parts of Aeternum to gather more knowledge. We stand at the dawn of a new age…
I’m afraid I must ask you for one final boon. Given what you’ve done, I feel almost selfish making this request. \n\nBut I would trust only you to undertake this most important task.
Ah, the precious parcel. I knew I would need this again someday. \n\nAnd now you deserve to see what it contains.
Have you spoken to Evandrus about Queen Cleopatra’s return? \n\nHis opinion is vital to swaying Ghazi.
Please help Ghazi to decide how best to serve the people of Brimstone Sands.
This is a great day for Brimstone Sands, and you have made it possible. \n\nI am glad the gods led you here.
This is a great day for Brimstone Sands, and you have made it possible. \n\nI am glad the gods led you here.
This is a great day for Brimstone Sands, and you have made it possible. \n\nI am glad the gods led you here.

It is good to see hope restored to these sands, but I must confess that I am troubled by the reactivation of the Ennead.\n\nKnowing that Artemis is involved and that she sought to raise Sutekh… it does not bode well.
It seems our work is never done. I've received word from a trusted ally named Lysandra. \n\nShe's been hearing rumors of strange tremors in the desert.
Keep your senses honed, my friend. \n\nI may need to travel to other parts of Aeternum to gather more knowledge. We stand at the dawn of a new age…

Stay together! There’s strength in numbers! 

Ready what weapons you have, but be prepared to run if it comes to that. Don’t lose hope!

[You must complete the Main Story quest "A Selfless Nature" in Edengrove to access the Main Story Quests in Brimstone Sands]
Stay together! There’s strength in numbers! \n\nReady what weapons you have, but be prepared to run if it comes to that. Don’t lose hope!
You there! You have a heroic look about you. \n\nThat steely glint in your eyes, the aura of confidence, the distinctive swagger.
I’m not only a scholar, I’m also a chronicler. \n\nFor the last several years, I’ve been committing to parchment the extraordinary life of none other than “Imhotep the Wise!”
Your bold and effective defense of these refugees has enraged the Legion garrison at Crassus’s Rise. \n\nThey’re preparing a massive assault to wipe us all out.
Luckily, my efforts to locate Imhotep have borne fruit! Aban sent a message that they were heading to Carthago. \n\nAban seemed especially worried about our master losing himself…
Luckily, my efforts to locate Imhotep have borne fruit! Aban sent a message that they were heading to Carthago. \n\nAban seemed especially worried about our master losing himself…
I knew something had gone wrong! I’m cursed with an infallible instinct for these sorts of things. \n\nDid you discover anything else in New Rhacotis?
I knew something had gone wrong! I’m cursed with an infallible instinct for these sorts of things. \n\nDid you discover anything else in New Rhacotis?
Please excuse the mess. Most of the important books and scrolls in the city were seized and stored here. \n\nIt’s become our library and our sanctum.
Please excuse the mess. Most of the important books and scrolls in the city were seized and stored here. \n\nIt’s become our library and our sanctum.
I have a feeling matters are about to get far more complicated. And not in a good way. \n\nI certainly hope we're both ready.
I have a feeling matters are about to get far more complicated. And not in a good way. \n\nI certainly hope we're both ready.
Comments: Conversation before/during 'Watering the Seed' in New Corsica

DefaultDialogue: I'll never forget your help in rescuing Imhotep. I’m in your debt. \n\nAlthough Imhotep's putting on a brave face, I still have worries. He's a tough old buzzard but even he has limits.
I'll never forget your help in rescuing Imhotep. I’m in your debt. \n\nAlthough Imhotep's putting on a brave face, I still have worries. He's a tough old buzzard but even he has limits.
Imhotep knows many arcane spells and secrets. \n\nHis mastery of Ancient magic is unrivaled on Aeternum.
You may witness all manner of sanity-bending events in Imhotep's presence. \n\nHe knows ancient secrets and magics that have not been witnessed by anyone for millennia.
Oh gods, it’s happened! Just as I feared it would! \n\nHis state of mind was far more fragile than he had let on. My poor master…
We must attend to the words of the Great Pharaoh. \n\nI know he seems different, but he's still Imhotep and wise beyond measure.
Being named the Great Pharaoh's Sword is an immense honor. He seems to have complete confidence in you. \n\nIf we are careful and make use of his will and determination, we may yet prevail here.
The Great Pharaoh is relying on you. Oh, who am I kidding? I'm relying on you. \n\nI don’t think we could’ve chosen a better champion. That's not too much pressure, is it?
The Pools of Orcus are a foul place. The fumes there sicken even the heartiest of individuals. \n\nTread carefully, Sword of Imhotep. The less time spent there, the better.
This mystery becomes more frightening with every step. \n\nI can't imagine where it's leading us, but my instinct tells me it's a terrifying place.
So you intend to enter Akhet? Imhotep built the great pyramid. \n\nWhatever happened there, it was enough to ensure he would never return. The Corrupted Legion seeks to claim its power.
The revelation of Sutekh's return has pushed Imhotep's mind to the edge! \n\nIf we lose him, we are truly doomed!
Imhotep’s obsessed with Sutekh’s return! He kept insisting he had to "prepare the way!" \n\nI’ve never seen him like this! He called himself the “Vizier of the Ancients!”
I don’t know about you, but I could use a hot bath and a nice long nap. \n\nSome company would be nice as well…
Bring your beautiful visage here and let me gaze upon you for a few moments! \n\nIt is so good to see you.
I’m sorry, I should have told you sooner. I wanted to. But I’ve been Ghazi for so long… \n\nMy actual name, the one I was given at birth, is Cleopatra.
I have considered what you and Imhotep have said. \n\nYou both sacrificed so much for this land. It is only fair that I do the same.
So, what did the people have to say?
So, what did the people have to say?
What are you doing? Didn’t your Queen command that you relax and enjoy yourself? \n\nEat, drink, dance. There's more to life than fighting monsters.
Your striking visage is always welcome, Sword of Brimstone. \n\nYou make the days brighter, and the nights sweeter.
Your striking visage is always welcome, Sword of Brimstone. \n\nYou make the days brighter, and the nights sweeter.

You look like a person who lives for excitement. Tell me my intuition is right! Life has been ever so dull around here. \n\nI tell you, Pontifex Charmion even shut down my plays! What is a city without a lively theatre scene?

Good riddance to that harpy Charmion! I'll be happier without her around. \n\nI know, I sound indelicate, but she threatened to behead me if I kept writing plays about her and Crassus. Beheading? Over a few jests!
I've been thinking about writing a new play about you. \n\nThe source material is a playwright's dream. Ambition, betrayal, tragedy, triumph… your story has it all!
Here for the arena? Out of luck. Pontifex shut it down. Nothing to do but sit, wait, and drink. \n\nCould go out there and fight the Legion, but fighting for sport's different from fighting for real.
Heard a lot about you adventurers lately. Sounds like a decent living. See places, meet people, fight monsters. \n\nNot sure if I could do it. Lost a lot over the years. Memories, skills, and people.
Arena might open again, with Charmion gone. Don't know if I'll stick around to see it. \n\nStill like the idea of doing what you do. Adventurer Mevia. There's a nice ring to it, don’t you think?

Cacti must be god's idea of a joke. They're too bitter to drink, too spiky to eat, and too tough to uproot. \n\nIf you ask me, Sutekh's to blame. He's the sort of god who'd litter the earth with useless, spiny plants.

I've brewed a new drink in honor of Queen Cleopatra's return. And you'll never guess what gives it color and flavor. \n\nCactus fruit! I've taste-tested every batch, and I guarantee it's a drink worthy of our beloved Queen.

My goodness, so many new arrivals these days. And your clothes are like nothing I've ever seen! \n\nOh, I know times are tough, but I can't help getting excited. We're long overdue for fresh faces in New Corsica.

Poor Evandrus. He's a brave man, coming back to face his demons. \n\nI offered him a gift of new tunics, but I don't think he feels comfortable out of his armor. It's hard to blame him, after what he's seen.

The Queen ordered some purple gowns for her wardrobe. Oh, what am I to do? \n\nNothing on this island produces color as rich as Tyrian purple. But I'll find a way. Nothing but the best for Queen Cleopatra.
No escape. No hope. No salvation from the red-eyed devils. T-they were at Shattered Mountain. On the shores. In the voices that howled. \n\nAnd n-now, here too? I c-can't fight them, not again!
I n-never was much good with a sword. \n\nFather was a rancher. M-maybe I could do the same, somewhere far from the f-fighting.

Let me guess. You saw a poor old woman alone in the desert, and thought she needed help hobbling back to town? \n\nPah! You townsfolk are all the same. I'm quite content here, far from all the noise and trouble.

So you've met the Insatiable Flame. That rascal tore up all my plants when he first showed up. \n\nThen he cowered like a kitten after I gave him a good scolding. He's quite sweet, as long as he's well-fed.
Tamouthis stopped by the other day. Said you put down the scorpion queen and her vile brood. \n\nMaybe you're all right for a city-dweller.
The moon and sun were one. Great Kronos peeled back the veil, and I saw the true nature of all things. \n\nThere are terrible holes in the world. Should we fall through, we will be devoured whole.

The boy does not know, yet he believes himself wise. I have stepped through the gates and lost my way. \n\nThey are not trifles for our convenience or amusement, no! But does he listen to poor, mad Titus? No one does!
You believe yourself victorious. It is but a respite. A moment of calm before the storm. \n\nAncient gods will blot out the sun. Their arms will cross the horizon and envelop the world in shadow.

The locals speak of a mighty wurm that burrows beneath the dunes. This land of blistering sun and biting wind has horrors aplenty, but so far I've seen no sign of the beast. \n\nIf you catch a glimpse of it, let me know. Its head will make a fine addition to my wall.

By God, I was such a fool to come here! A few nights ago, I saw the face of the great wurm. \n\nI fell to my knees and waited for the end. But it passed without taking my life. Why? Why did it spare me?
Finally, someone with the sense to bring their own supplies. \n\nNot that I'd have much to give you if you didn't. We're short of everything useful around here.
I heard about your exploits at the Great Pyramid. The whole camp talks of nothing else. \n\nYou can't seem to keep yourself out of trouble, friend. The world-ending, earth-shaking sort of trouble.
You're no soldier. Were we friends, or foes? I… can't recall your face, but I hope you're here to help. \n\nThe Legion was supposed to protect people. And we did, long ago.
Evandrus. I remember… the day I told him I was retiring. He smiled at me, the happiest smile I've ever seen. \n\nNow we're both back in armor, fighting, with no more smiles between us.
Is it over? I can go back to my farm, and let this fade into the fog of memory. \n\nWell, I hope I won't forget you. You were kind, brave, and true. Everything I wanted to be as a Legionnaire.

Devastation and ruin as far as the eye can see, and no one to lead us through it. \n\nNo matter how fervently we prayed, the gods refused to give us peace and quiet. We'll only find help in each other.
I wondered when Charmion would show her true face. \n\nHmph. The less said about her, the better.

Are the rumors true? Has Queen Cleopatra herself returned to us? Part of me yearns to see her splendor. \n\nBut I wasted so many years in New Corsica, under Charmion's thumb. Better to stay here and help where I can.
I've lost two carts, several priceless heirlooms, and my best sandals since leaving New Corsica. \n\nFortuna is a cruel mistress, but she could always take more from me.

Things seem to be going well, but I think my time in this land is coming to a close. Call it business intuition or wanderlust. \n\nHmm… I've never been to Ebonscale Reach. That sounds like a good change of scenery.
I hope you haven't come in search of healing. I will do my very best, but I have little to work with. \n\nPeople on Aeternum are so careless toward their own health. It's frightful to see.

Someday, I'd like to learn how to use a Life Staff. I thought the locals were exaggerating when they told me about it. \n\nThe power to heal injuries and soothe pain with a wave of your hands… it's like something out of a legend.
Take care of yourself, friend. After all your heroic struggles, I think you've earned a breather. \n\nWe may live forever, but we're still human. We need rest and care, and you're no exception.

So many abandoned valuables, so little time. People leave the most incredible things behind. \n\nOh, judge not lest ye be judged, friend. Besides, I doubt the Lost or Corrupted need their earthly treasures.

With the Legion no longer on the rampage, it's easier than ever to scavenge things. \n\nBut I loved the danger, every second of it. There's nothing like the rush of barely escaping with your life. You can relate, right?

Hah! It seems the New Corsicans finally listened to me, and sent another professional to do their killing. \n\nWelcome to this little piece of hell, friend. There's no shortage of danger, and plenty of work for two.

I hear Evandrus is trying to rehabilitate his father's image. Wonder how much of the eulogizing is true. \n\nPeople are awfully quick to put words in the mouths of the departed, if you catch my drift.
If Cleopatra needs mercenaries, put in a word for me. Things got mighty quiet around here. \n\nGood for everyone else, bad for me. I get bored when the fighting dies down.
This desert air is terrible for my tools, to say nothing of my skin. \n\nWhat I wouldn't give for a proper university workshop.
You don't look like a local. I was hoping I might bend your ear for an unusual request. \n\nNothing illegal, I promise. Let's simply call it... destructive investigation.
Sulfur, mercury, gypsum glass, but this fourth element eludes me. Some kind of refined azoth? How does it remain stable? \n\nAh, it's you! As you can see, the scarab power sources keep me very busy.
W-Who are you?! Stay back, don't come any closer! \n\nAugh… I really hope you aren't a bandit. Though if you are, I don't have much for you to take.

Before you appeared, I didn't think strangers would show us any kindness. The gods might have abandoned us, but you didn't. \n\nThanks again, friend. I'll remember you when I'm well enough to hunt again.
Oh, mighty Jupiter, have mercy on me!
Naught left but feathers and blood. At this rate I'll be ruined, though we'll all starve first. Now there's a cheery thought.\n\nWhat are you looking at? A woman at her wits' end, that's what.
Naught left but feathers and blood. At this rate I'll be ruined, though we'll all starve first. Now there's a cheery thought.\n\nWhat are you looking at? A woman at her wits' end, that's what.
Naught left but feathers and blood. At this rate I'll be ruined, though we'll all starve first. Now there's a cheery thought.\n\nWhat are you looking at? A woman at her wits' end, that's what.
I'll say this for the New Corsicans. They're a hardy lot. Despite the Legion and the wild beasts, the camp's held together. \n\nPerhaps I'll stay a while longer, at least until I get back on my feet.
What a fine mess. I'll be lucky if I ever find him. \n\nOh, why did that storm have to strike now?
I'm sorry to trouble you, but did you see a man wash up on the southern shore? \n\nI was awaiting his arrival, but then his ship crashed during the storm. I saw it all happen!
I'm sorry to trouble you, but did you see a man wash up on the southern shore? \n\nI was awaiting his arrival, but then his ship crashed during the storm. I saw it all happen!
You'll be glad to hear that no more of the Empress's ships have sailed this way. \n\nI would dearly love to return home. But this Corrupted Legion... they worry me.
These rough conditions are utterly beneath me. Do you know who I am? \n\nFroderico Renaldi, renowned scholar of the classics! You may know me from my treatise about Marius's reforms.
They killed me! How dare they! Stabbed me through and tossed me over the palisade like a rag doll! \n\nOh, the indignity of it all…
I began working on a new book, about textiles and evolving fashion among the Roman exiles. \n\nIt may be a less prestigious topic, but looms are less likely to stab me to death.
Will she ever forgive me? \n\nHer Excellency isn't known for her charitable nature, but this humble servant can hope for her favor.
(The armadillo gives you a single, disdainful sniff before looking away.)
We have strayed from the ways of our ancestors. \n\nAnd in return, the curse of the Lost is ours to bear.

Memory fades with each passing year, and none remember the old rituals. \n\nI wouldn't expect such things to matter to an outsider. But to those who try to honor the gods, it is of profound importance.
What incantation do I try next? To whom do I pray? \n\nSomeone must hear our prayers. If not… no, I dare not entertain the thought.
Hrrm? A delicious passing morsel? No, you look rather too large and uncomfortable to eat. \n\nWhy do you stare? Do you WANT to be my dinner?
A human? Ah, my favorite human, the bringer of fish. \n\nMay your sunbeams be warm, your catches plentiful, and your belly full.
According to this map, the ruin's a bit further up the cliff. \n\nOh, I should've asked for directions before wandering out here.
Ah, a fellow traveler! This may strike you as an odd question, but have you ever seen a dragon on this mountainside? \n\nTo be clear, I speak of the variety with large wings and flaming breath.
Thanks to you, I'm overflowing with ideas for my sculptures. Why stop at dragon eggs? \n\nThe well-to-do of Aeternum may want a unicorn horn, or a manticore stinger to hang over their fireplaces.
I can't help watching the Great Pyramid out of the corner of my eye. Do you know what holds it aloft? \n\nNeither do I. I don't like the thought one bit.
Another mercenary. The deserts have been lousy with you lot. \n\nPick up a survey map and make yourself useful. How's your hearing?
The tremors continue, but I've yet to see the creature emerge above ground. \n\nA few other travelers mentioned sightings, but I told them to keep their distance.
I've had it with my family! My mother, my uncles, the whole decrepit lot of them. \n\nMust I throw myself over the cliffs to make them see sense? Will anything put a stop to their tiresome meddling?
You're also new to this place, aren't you? \n\nThe monuments and statues are impressive, but I'll never forget the first time I saw a Greek play. I laughed until my sides ached!
Please don't disturb an old man's peaceful retirement.\n\nI believe I've earned some quiet.
The Ancients must have been giants compared to us. \n\nLook at the size of these steps, the monumental perfection of each stone block! One can only wonder at the secrets they contain.
I'll have a limp for weeks. Monsieur Heron makes scrambling up and down ancient ruins sound so easy! \n\nOh, I beg your pardon. I'm just recovering from an embarrassing fall.
Have you seen the circular stone gates at Hermopolis? There is one just like them, right above our heads. \n\nBut no matter what I do, the gateway here remains inactive.
Do you think Monsieur Heron would be interested in collaborating with me? \n\nMy knowledge of languages pales next to his. I should brush up on my Latin, but I've never found book learning easy.
Mind your step, traveler. \n\nThe little scorpions are easy to skewer, but the big ones get the better of many overconfident hunters.
I've heard the most fantastic rumors about you. \n\nSo, you should have no trouble with a large swarm of angry scorpions.
The creatures of the wilds are not to be feared, but understood. \n\nThat lesson's lost on most, but not you. It's nice to meet a kindred spirit.
Those pillars look much taller up close. \n\nWell, they aren't getting any shorter by staring at them. I hope these old legs will carry me the rest of the way.
Phew, finally got away from all those guardians. \n\nBut now what? I can't leave until my mission's complete, but I can't fight through the Ancient guardians either…
A fellow Soulwarden out here? Well, I won't look a gift horse in the mouth. \n\nCare to help our brethren one more time? Don't worry, this is a blessing for us… I hope.

I thought the ruins in Everfall were impressive, but that was before I laid eyes on the Wall. \n\nI'll bet that it hides even more secrets. Try going back from time to time, and see if anything else opens up for you.
You are far from civilization, stranger. \n\nIndulge me in an odd question: how adept are you at handling great beasts of the desert?
You again? The sacrifice has been accepted, and we can only pray that the gods stay their wrath. \n\nGo, now. I have no more coin or treasure for you.
(The jackal's piercing eyes look you over from head to toe.)
Jabir ibn Hayyan posits a balance of sulfur and mercury, but the potency of local sulfur overwhelms mercury and disrupts the normal methods of transmutation. \n\nWhat a delightful little puzzle!
All these excavations, and for what? \n\nFor all our efforts at enlightenment, we seem to reap nothing but dust.
New Corsica, ancient bastion of knowledge and hidden secrets. \n\nI find this place suits me, though I wish travel by spirit shrines wasn't so nauseating.
How goes your search for the Ancient glyphs? \n\nI've been tracking down local rumors of their locations, but it's tedious work sorting the wheat from the chaff.

Your dedication to knowledge may even come close to my own. And you're much better suited to exploring dangerous locales. \n\nI am in your debt. When I uncover more about the glyphs or the language's secrets, you will be the first to know.
This bag was almost buried by the sands. \n\nIt contains several small portraits on wood, a half-full waterskin, and a brittle note.
This small, weathered statue appears unremarkable.
It's hard to make out the writing on this ancient tablet. \n\nYou can only pick out three words: Ennead, pilgrimage, power.
Please… help me… aahhh… please…
Please… help me… aahhh… please…
Hearken to the words of the blessed Pontifex Charmion! She speaks for the gods and dispenses their wisdom!
New Corsica welcomes you, pilgrim. \n\nIf you wish an audience with the blessed Pontifex Charmion, you must meditate on the wisdom of the Sacred Scroll of Awakening.
Prayer alone will not save us! The gods require deeds! \n\nWords without action are empty!

The people of New Corsica need a better way forward. Not a new faith, but a fresh interpretation for changing times. \n\nWith my knowledgeable guidance, of course. I've no intention of going anywhere.
Attend the words of the Pontifex Nuru. Her wisdom will guide us into a new age of enlightenment. \n\nI'm sure you're as eager as I am to witness such a miracle.
Comments: Dejected after not being named Pontifex

DefaultDialogue: You would be an excellent candidate for the Marauders. \n\nIf you wish to join our battles, I welcome you with open arms.
We never run out of foes to fight and victories to win. \n\nThis vicious island suits us Marauders.
You'll want Adjudicator Teos, not me. \n\nI never was much of an orator.
Talk to Alchemist Euphrosyne if you must. \n\nI never have any idea what you Syndicate are talking about.
There are no pretenses among us Marauders. \n\nYou're here for gold, battle, and glory, and I have opportunites aplenty.
Others see eternal life as a curse, but not the seekers of the Syndicate. \n\nEndless years to learn, understand, and plumb the mysteries of the world. What could be better?
Welcome, welcome. \n\nThere are enough mysteries in this land to keep both of us occupied.
We're not so different, you and I. \n\nAll you need is a little more curiosity about the light you so fervently safeguard.
Don't you ever wonder if there's more to life than battle and bloodshed? \n\nIf so, you know where to find me.
Someday, we'll rival the works of the Ancients themselves. \n\nWe will be the architects of our own paradise, right here on Aeternum.
Are you lost, friend? We all are, in one way or another. \n\nBut some of us choose to join the Covenant and find our way through the darkness, together.
We sing the song of hope on an island of strife. \n\nI know it seems a thankless task at times, but you are never alone. The light of others shines with you.
A Marauder? If you're here to pick a fight, I must decline. \n\nThis is not the time or place.
For those who claim to know so much, you Syndicate understand little. \n\nFarewell.
It's easy to give in to one's base impulses. Violence, greed, naked ambition. \n\nBut you rise above such things. You are an inspiration to us all.
You're strong, traveler, but you'd be stronger with Marauders at your side. \n\nCome on, I promise we don't bite. Much.
I've heard the wildest tales about your battles, friend. \n\nIf even half are true, you could cross blades with the legends of old!
You here for a drink? How about a fight? \n\nTch, you Covenant are all work and no play.
Hello. How's your disturbing research going? \n\nWhat? That's what the Syndicate does, right?
Having you around has really livened this place up. \n\nI hope you stay a while, friend. Our victories will be the stuff of legend!
Return when you are ready to be inducted in the arcane mysteries of the Syndicate. \n\nUntil then, we have nothing to discuss.
With each new discovery, our understanding deepens, and our power grows. \n\nThe quest never ends, fellow seeker.
Open your mind to the infinite possibilities of the cosmos. \n\nPerhaps then, we can talk.
We have nothing for you, Marauder. \n\nSeek your simple pleasures elsewhere.
The day is coming, fellow seeker. \n\nThat sublime dawn when knowledge sets us free, and mankind breaks all its shackles.
No one, no matter how strong, should be without allies. \n\nRemember that, traveler.
Welcome home, friend. \n\nThe divine calls to us with many different voices, but we of the Covenant answer as one.
Valor is nothing without a higher purpose.
Wisdom comes with compassion, not ambitious grasping.
Aeternum is a land in desperate need of hope, love, and protection. \n\nWe provide it through our service. Never doubt that, friend.
(The chest is empty. The Eye of Horus is gone.)
(The chest is empty. The Eye of Horus is gone.)
Where are you? You should have at least sent word by now… \n\nI'm sorry, friend. Something important has my attention right now. Perhaps later?

You've made it! Good! Your exploits precede you, and we have need of your aid. \n\nIn addition to the threat from the Tempest's forces here, we received word that the Corrupted Legion in Brimstone Sands is preparing an assault on the capital of New Corsica. The civilians are fleeing the region in droves in advance of the fight.

You smell like dust and heat, friend! I assume you made it into the deserts of Brimstone Sands without too much difficulty. And Buhawi? \n\nYou've taken a weight off my shoulders! Thank you for checking up on him.
Where are you? You should have at least sent word by now… \n\nI'm sorry, friend. Something important has my attention right now. Perhaps later?

You smell like dust and heat, friend! I assume you made it into the deserts of Brimstone Sands without too much difficulty. And Buhawi? \n\nYou've taken a weight off my shoulders! Thank you for checking up on him.

Tomash is a bit overprotective at times. Just means he cares. But helping people is what I'm meant to do, no matter the danger. \n\nCorruption, Lost, an Ancient device… doesn't matter. I am a warrior, a defender, and I will stand between the darkness and the light!

Tomash is a bit overprotective at times. Just means he cares. But helping people is what I'm meant to do, no matter the danger. 

Corruption, Lost, an Ancient device… doesn't matter. I am a warrior, a defender, and I will stand between the darkness and the light!

[You must complete the Main Story quest "A Selfless Nature" in Edengrove to access the Main Story Quests in Brimstone Sands]

Tomash is a bit overprotective at times. Just means he cares. But helping people is what I'm meant to do, no matter the danger. \n\nCorruption, Lost, an Ancient device… doesn't matter. I am a warrior, a defender, and I will stand between the darkness and the light!
Welcome, welcome! Please, there is plenty of room.\n\nHave a seat by the fire, or take a rest if you'd like.
You're brave, traveler. Not many come this way by choice.\n\nWe've bunks in the tent, if you need to rest for a while.

I'm not sure why you've come here. You cannot stop what I have begun.

The threat of Corruption was dire, but the toll you exacted from the Motherwell, the damage you wrought... it will take generations to heal.

I foolishly came to the aid of humanity, and once again, this is how we were repaid.

It is proven again, Humanity is the true source of all evils, a vessel for Corruption, a plague to nature, and you are a prime example.

Another of my kind lies dreaming in these sands, but he will soon be awakened.

And together, we will purge this island of your kind and restore Aeternum to the paradise it was meant to be. Begone from here. There is nothing you can do.
Brimstone Sands has been my home for centuries. \n\nI refuse to leave with nothing to remember the place where I finally found love and happiness.

I tried to leave, I really did. I had every intention! When I reached this camp, my heart demanded I stop. \n\nHere in this desert, I found everything I wanted in life, and I cannot leave empty-handed.
I feel more optimistic about my journey now, free to remember the love I had… but still able to move forward.
These sands, they move… in a most unnatural way. Do you see? There! They quiver with energy. Dark days are coming…

Careful for your step, traveler. The sands, they come alive! The earth strikes back with angry vengeance! \n\nI wrote the scrolls, in my own hand, but even I had come to doubt such horrors ever existed… until now.
You may be the only hope this desert has.
The 19th Legion should be remembered with honor, with reverence, not with terror and disgust.

Know this, friend. The 19th Legion was not always dedicated to darkness. It was once the most valiant legion in all of Rome. \n\nThe 19th stayed loyal to Mark Antony even as Alexandria fell. They escorted Antony and the Queen here…
Progress on that damned statue has really been set back after your assault. \n\nWell done, friend!
Believe it or not, our people once thought it was from this Temple that the sun was set afire each day.

Behold the glorious Lamp of Osiris, wayfarer! This sacred temple was once believed to be where the gods set the sun afire each day. \n\nThe fallacy of our faith was exposed centuries ago, but the Temple should still be ours.
It is a tragedy we were blocked from so many of the sacred temples we once helped to build. \n\nBut you retrived the Spark of Osiris, and that is something indeed.
If you're headed towards Jupiter's Grove, beware. The dangers of the grove have multiplied in a matter of weeks. \n\nElementals now haunt the place, and they are vengeful towards humanity.
You there, are you by chance headed into Jupiter's Grove? Are you aware of what's befallen that site? \n\nThe Grove is now overrun with Elemental entities, and I cannot get by them.
Habibah sent word that the waters of the thermae once again restore the health of all guests to New Corsica. \n\nThank you for your help. And of course for your utmost discretion on this matter.
